              Lorenzo Maria Convenevole has these emails:<br>lanceg@tiscalinet.it<br>fn074354@flashnet.it<br>l.convenevole@flashnet.it <br>alfozonzo@katamail.com<br><br>This guy is a scammer and has not delivered.  He had better hope I never visit his country or hell is break out on his ass.<br><br>His primary Internet Service Provider appears to be flashnet.it which appears to have recently been acquired by CyberNet at http://www.cyb.it/<br>I have sent an email message to CyberNet today to inform them of the Internet fraud that has been committed by Lorenzo.<br><br>The reason I know of the additional emails is because of two reasons.  The first one lanceg@tiscalinet.it was used to bid on one of Lorenzo's own auctions to increase his status at Player Auctions.  This is the link to that bid:<br>http://www.playerauctions.com/listings/details/index.cfm?itemnum=998474792<br><br>lanceg@tiscalinet.it was confirmed by another person that made a purchase from this guy but did not receive the item until weeks later and he was told that lanceg@tiscalinet.it was his additional email.<br><br>fn074354@flashnet.it was used to bid on Lorenzo's own auction to increase his status at:<br>http://www.playerauctions.com/listings/details/index.cfm?itemnum=998473688<br><br>I sent an email to fn074354@flashnet.it and received a reply that had the return email address as l.convenevole@flashnet.it  <br>He had forgotten to change his return email when he replied to me.  This is the mistake he made that linked him to flashnet.it<br>Since then, he has sent two additional replies.  The last one had his return email address changed back to fn074354@flashnet.it because he  found it and made the change.<br><br>The Western Union customer service number in Italy is 39 06 3671 9302<br>Western Union confirmed that he picked up the money at:<br>Store name: Bettini Alessandro<br>Address: Via Vittorio Veneto Number 4<br><br><br>__________________________________________________________________________________________<br>*** FRAUD ALERT *** alfozonzo@katamail.com<br><br>Do not buy or sell anything with the following person.  He will rip you off as he did me.  Here are his details:<br><br>His email that he's used on playerauctions.com is alfozonzo@katamail.com<br>He also uses an alias email of lanceg@tiscalinet.it<br><br>Lorenzo Maria Convenevole<br>Date of Birth: 18 April 1973<br>Rome, Italy<br><br>The phone number he gave me is Country Code 39 and number 03280754758<br><br>He has posted the sale of two characters on playerauctions.com and has not delivered either of them.  He is a liar and will not deliver what he has promised.  If you have any information about this person, please send email to nickolaismith@hotmail.com<br><br>The two characters that were not delivered are:<br><br>http://www.playerauctions.com/listings/details/index.cfm?itemnum=1000803961<br>http://www.playerauctions.com/listings/details/index.cfm?itemnum=1000822666<br><br>I have paid cash at a Western Union office and had the money delivered to Rome, Italy to the person shown above.  I am going to post this every where that I can.  Any ideas on where I should post this to let people know about this injustice?  I don't want this guy doing this ever again especially all of you here that value your hard earned money.  I have also read the post made 'LoL' (stranger) and am reposting here because it's good information to try to prevent frauds in the future:<br><br> 1) Verify the account or item is real..If he/she will not meet you in the game..or misses several times...end it right then forget him.<br> 2) Talk with him/her on the phone..If any conflicts like misses the call or etc...end it forget about the deal..SAVE YOUR MONEY!!! <br> 3) If he/she is pushy "I have other bidders wanting this" or any thing that just sounds like he/she is trying to force the sale...RUN RUN RUN DONT BUY!!!.                 <br> 4) If you can use paypal, ensure that you change the "Funding Options" to your credit card.  If using Western Union, use www.westernunion.com and use your credit card to send payment ...and make sure to use the show ID option. <br> 5) If you use paypal make sure you only buy from a verified/confirmed address..with your credit card..not paypal funds or bank funds.  When the payment amount is greater than your PayPal account balance, you can change the payment method (i.e. from Instant Transfer to eCheck or Credit Card) by clicking the "Funding Options" link under the "Source of Funds" heading on the payment confirmation page.  When you use a credit card, you have the option of contacting the credit card company and letting them know of the purchase without delivery if the person doesn't deliver what was auctioned.<br> 6) Ask for references if he/she has any...when you have them on the phone ask several questions to the referal is possible..if the seller wont give you a few days to get this done..most likey you should run run run. <br> 7) And most importantly use the email address to "track" his history on other sites like ebay, yahoo etc..since most of the time if he/she is a scammer..they're trying this on more then just this site.<br> 8) If you're buying a character, ensure the person uses postal mail to send you the original Everquest, Kunark and Velious CD's with the CD-Keys included.<br>_________________________________________________________________________________________<br><br><br><br>
